modules.description: This module offers combinators to convert OCaml values into syntactically valid representations, handling basic types like integers and booleans, optional and result types, and user-defined types with configurable constructor formatting. It supports structured data including tuples (up to 10 elements), lists, sequences, arrays, and records, enabling custom printer composition for debugging multicore workflows and generating test-case syntax in property-based testing with QCheck integration.

This module provides equality functions for comparing values of common types like integers, strings, options, lists, and exceptions. It supports constructing equality checks for composite types using combinators such as `equal_option`, `equal_list`, and `equal_result`. These functions are useful for writing precise assertions in test cases that involve value comparisons.

This module supports multicore testing with functions to repeat property checks, enforce timeouts, and fork properties in separate processes. It includes utilities to format and compare structured data, with support for custom printers and equality checks. Use cases include debugging parallel execution traces, validating non-deterministic behavior, and generating readable test output.
